# Shell scripts MUST stay LF in the working copy. The Docker bash toolchain
# (tools/_portspike/_p6/build_*.sh) breaks on CRLF line-continuation
# (`\<CR><LF>` -> "syntax error near unexpected token"). With core.autocrlf=true
# git was re-mangling these to CRLF on every checkout/stash, so they had to be
# hand-renormalized after each git op. This rule pins them LF permanently and
# retires that recurring trap.
*.sh text eol=lf
